Part 1 - Creating tidy data using tidyr

Tuition<- pivot_longer(tuition_cost, c("2017", "2018", "2019", "2020"), names_to = "Year", values_to = "tuition")
Tuition<- separate(Tuition, tuition, into= c("InState", "OutState"), sep= '/')
Tuition$InState<- as.integer(Tuition$InState)
Tuition$OutState<- as.integer(Tuition$OutState)
head(Tuition)

Part 2 - North Carolina Schools

Public<- Tuition %>%
  filter(state %in% "North Carolina") %>%
  filter(type %in% "Public") %>%
  filter(degree_length %in% "4 Year")

ggplot(Public, aes(Year, InState, color= name)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "In-State Tuition for North Carolina Schools",x=" Year", y= "Cost in $" ) +
  scale_fill_discrete(name = "  ")

For somew reason I can not change the legend name. It is very aggravating.

UNC <- filter(Public,grepl("University of North Carolina",name)) 
ggplot(UNC, aes(Year, InState, color= name)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "In-State Tuition for UNC Schools",x= "Year" , y= "Cost in $") +
  theme(legend.position="bottom") + 
guides(colour = guide_legend(nrow = 4))

Part 3 - Additional Universities

Colorado<- Tuition %>%
  select(name, state, type, degree_length, Year, OutState) %>%
  filter(state %in% "Colorado") %>%
  filter(type %in% "Public") %>%
  filter(degree_length %in% "4 Year")

South_Carolina<- Tuition %>%
  select(name, state, type, degree_length, Year, InState) %>%
  filter(state %in% "South Carolina") %>%
  filter(type %in% "Public") %>%
  filter(degree_length %in% "2 Year")

ggplot(Colorado, aes(Year, OutState, color= name)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Out of State Tuition for Colorado Schools",x= "Year" , y= "Cost in $") +
  theme(legend.position="bottom") + 
guides(colour = guide_legend(nrow = 8))

ggplot(South_Carolina, aes(Year, InState, color= name)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "In-State Tuition for South Carolina Schools",x= "Year" , y= "Cost in $") +
  theme(legend.position="bottom") + 
guides(colour = guide_legend(nrow = 7))
